content: TLDR: Orlando is a city known for its world-renowned theme parks, attracting millions of visitors each year. Whether you're a water park enthusiast, a Disney fanatic, a thrill-seeker, or just looking for some family fun, Orlando's theme parks have something for everyone. To make the most out of your visit, it's essential to plan ahead and stay in one of the nearby neighborhoods or towns, such as Lake Buena Vista, Davenport, Kissimmee, Windsor Hills, or Four Corners. And don't forget to check out the map of Orlando's theme parks and attractions to make navigating easier.
